lenders.name: Gwendolen
lenders.occupation: Entrepreneur / Author / Public Speaker / Creative Artist
lenders.loan_because:
First, I am my mother's, Mrs. Espanolia McCloud, daughter; thus the reason I share my profile picture with her. 

From an early age she taught me compassion for others and that we all have value and purpose. She was a woman who made the earth a better place wherever she traveled and, while our family was poor, she brought a richness to my life that cannot be expressed in words. She was my world, the meaning behind every breathe I took as a child when she was alive and since her passing in 1980. In fact, the principles of sharing she taught me are at the foundation of all my entrepreneurial endeavors; after all, the point of life is to help others up during one's rise. And while an undying belief in one's talents and abilities are essential to starting and sustaining a business, so too is money. Therefore, I support the businesses on Kiva because my mother taught me the importance and power of sharing; her spirit living in every donation.
lenders.occupational_info:
Entrepreneur

In November 2009, I officially founded McCloud9 Enterprises, LLC (www.gwenmccloud.com), a company that specializes in real estate investing and virtual assisting for companies in the areas of real estate, entertainment, event planning, marketing, research, legal, staffing, nonprofit, government, and the military. I am currently in the process of establishing a nonprofit division that will offer affordable housing and nice used cars to low-income and other deserving individuals. As it pertains to my goal as a business owner, it is to leave a legacy of sharing where I help others realize their full personal and professional potential.

Author / Public Speaker / Creative Artist

I have been writing poetry since the age of 10, and speaking/performing since eighteen. My writing portfolio includes short stories of fantasy, poetry, novels, essays, plays, and children’s stories - a total of 100 works to date, with my first self-publication being "Cake Tales: 10 Deliriously Delicious Stories of the Surreal." As it pertains to my speaking repertoire, I have given a total of sixty-one (61) speeches/performances.  When creating a literary work or presenting a performance speech, my desire is to educate, entertain, motivate, and empower the audience. My live performances, which are creative medleys of speech, poetry, song, and movement, include: Opened for Ossie Davis and Ruby Dee (Otelia Cromwell Day, Smith College); Media One Talent Showcase; The Department of Justice Martin Luther King Day Celebration; National Black Arts Festival; Uptown Comedy Corner; Sweet Auburn Festival; Culture Center; Patti Hut; Have a Heart Benefit; Harlem Renaissance (Amherst College); Black History Celebration Event (Southern Polytechnic State University); Images of Sound (Augustus Savage Art Gallery at the University of Massachusetts at Amherst). In addition to writing and delivering performance speeches, I am also an experienced actress (comedic and dramatic) of both stage and film. While writing, speaking/performing, and acting are my primary artistic endeavors, my talents also include singing, doll-making, drawing, cooking, and dancing.
